article.description: Garvey Young and Maurice Joseph scored 14 points apiece to help Vermont beat Boston University 78-58 for its sixth straight win on Sunday.
article.headline: Early turnovers, poor shooting cost Boston U. fifth win in row
article.linkText: Slow start dooms Boston U. in loss to Vermont
article.story: BURLINGTON, Va. -- Garvey Young and Maurice Joseph scored 14 points apiece to help Vermont beat Boston University 78-58 for its sixth straight win on Sunday. The Catamounts (13-5, 4-0 America East Conference) opened the game strong, taking a 20-2 lead on Garrett Kissel's layup with 10 minutes left in the first half. The Terriers (9-9, 4-2) turned the ball over four times and shot 1-for-14 in the opening 10 minutes. Vermont, which had 11 players score, had 18 assists and just eight turnovers. The Catamounts outrebounded Boston U. 42-31 and scored 20 second chance points. Marqus Blakely scored 11 points and Evan Fjeld added 10 for the Catamounts, who have won 10 of their last 11. The Terriers, who trailed 33-14 at halftime, shot just 16.7 percent in the first half. John Holland scored 21 points and Corey Lowe added 18 for Boston U., which snapped a four-game winning streak.
